Funny that #10, 'Comments that explain the “how” but not the “why”', quotes from an article by Jeff Atwood to show how the comment should have been written. But in the original article, Jeff actually says that <i>that</i> commenting style is also not as good as refactoring the code:<p>"That must be what I was getting at, right? Some sort of pleasant, middle-of-the-road compromise between the two polar extremes of no comments whatsoever and carefully formatted epic poems every second line of code?<p>Not exactly. Rather than add a comment, I'd refactor to this:<p><pre><code>  private double SquareRootApproximation(n) {
    r = n / 2;
    while ( abs( r - (n/r) ) > t ) {
      r = 0.5 * ( r + (n/r) );
    }
    return r;
  }
  System.out.println( "r = " + SquareRootApproximation(r) ); "</code></pre>
